    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-06-21T04:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-06-21T04:00:00-05:00" n="684"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d684">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">393.1111 Bush, Henry J./35: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul at Canton</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Fletcher</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Canton</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-06-21T17:00:00+08:00"
                            >June 21, 1935—5 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received June 21—3:15 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Father Henry J. Bush officially delivered by Marshall Chen Chi Tang<note n="9"
                        xml:id="d684fn9">Director of peace preservation at Canton.</note> to this
                    Consulate General 3 p.m. today. Bush in good health notwithstanding 7 weeks’
                    captivity and upon his request was placed on afternoon express train for Hong
                    Kong accompanied by Father Charles P. Hilbert. Bush ascribes his release
                    entirely to the strenuous efforts of the three first group army divisions
                    mobilized by Marshal Chen Chi Tang for Bush’s rescue. Repeated to the
                    Department, the Legation, Swatow and to Nanking.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Fletcher</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
